[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java 9 Constructor Behavior**\n\nI'm wondering if the Java 9 constructor initializes the sunMiscUnsafe field before the constructor itself runs. Fields seem to initialize in order, with stack/getCallerClass and then sunMiscUnsafe using getReferencedUnsafe(), which is declared before the constructor. But it looks like it's assigned after the constructor body. This feels a bit complex, and I need clarity on how initialization order works in this case. It’s interesting to unpack these details!\n\n**Considering Java Constructor Details**\n\nI’m thinking about the Java source constructor, which takes two parameters (usf and meth). It looks like the bytecode has a synthetic outer first, and there’s the question if MethodHandles for the inner constructor include the outer first. Yes, they do — especially in Java 9 with TheUnsafe and MethodHandle. I’m also considering whether I need to use `Class.forName(\"javassist.util.proxy.SecurityActions$TheUnsafe\")`. It’s a bit of a complex situation!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_067293e447af4bdf0169ef55fea980819c900f500990a3e164\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp71YxW5OvIgp8oC_4XizgJKDWnrWANVmrsql1BezaXJq4hFDULjwDSlsfXg6bzL2Eki5ndB5fydomIKYBlOj9I4beR5nPkH1JurxqL6GJ7f9AUqqL_N_jQ-7sc-BbVbpmoivUtiwtjYnSyqC3kEmj634d3ESOGeCelLLsXA5zui65cOZgmv6vJHpRo-HYRW0bxWl3UuQQQ2VJ4P5y1KNHYKKyxfXhqNfq8HLPL6hBy8fUb6FsEJVpUXCNZRTazp7mHHFgR9kcb70Nw6UDz6FUsa6pJbcONXd1GAgfm9RJ0nzVck0bXGEaUbIFz-DExXDGKn7lWiZLnJo-0bXQED6alq8dN_enXm3sxoOdA_lCVW3Ue6C38iCijdEMT45kgpNtf5-5pdX0JBWsbWlsOw8lPddijBK-g_CyqpFBduZVyTKdMGYHyO-H7RLtLmhCN6CPNghXMXsh6mMEhKl2QHjionfHAwAdwrwL2Jn9vdR4V0JuWUJCKIT9SbplQG4-r4qK9STpQL5-X07ZApUtaHvgG9v9Zkt6BXOPQt7BFU4FZHo5nu_9nKFdm0PIpWh-xwkR1PCuKrVBQNPwghWQTMEpeZ0sK-I07PWQOhdNUVUpN1W2oEzkFiGxXQUVxRpSyF89jCAgYpRBzwdrYyUBehV1AwkMBKxAcN1qyHb7OtciaT01YMEhuP9aFxsGcIVO5nR4ICDFYS4Kn4j0WwUUzLcbYsmYZTnjd